JSON Server

- Construir o backend com o JSON Server
- Cadastrar novas categorias no db.json
- Listagemi de categorias




Subir servidor backend + front
________________________________________


Local

1. Configurar o arquivo packege.json
  "scripts": {
    // Ddentificando o db.json como backend na porta 6060 (Retirar Coment√°rio)
    "server": "json-server --watch db.json --port 6060",
    //Rodando o concurrently para subir o back e front
    "dev": "concurrently \"react-scripts start\" \"npm run server\"",
    "start": "react-scripts start",
    "build": "react-scripts build",
    "test": "react-scripts test",
    "eject": "react-scripts eject"
  },


2. npm install json-server
3. npm install --save-dev concurrently
4. yarn install
5. yarn run dev


Server - HIROKU (https://heroku.com)

1. criar arquivo server.js na raiz do projeto
2. configurar o arquivo packege.json
  "scripts": {
    "server": "node ./server.js",
    "dev": "concurrently \"react-scripts start\" \"npm run server\"",
    "start": "npm run server",
    "build": "react-scripts build",
    "test": "react-scripts test",
    "eject": "react-scripts eject"
  },
  3 .



